race.comment: FLAMING EYES (7) keeps finding one or two better but is absolutely bursting to win one. Has savaged the line in her last three and now draws to take much closer order. With Holder sticking, she gets every chance to finally put them away. TERMINAL SHOCK (10) has built the right platform and should be nearing her peak now fourth-up. Will likely drift back from the gate and be saved for one last crack late. HE'S THE RUMOUR (8) took a clear step forward last start when flashing home into fourth at Strathalbyn. Has further improvement to come and is another who'll be strong late. THAVMA (5) can be inconsistent but was solid last start over the mile, sticking on gamely into the placings. Draws well again and should be around the mark. MOUSSAKA (4) improved second-up and looks another who can lift further with the rise in trip. Don't dismiss.
